WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:07.133 --> 00:00:10.136
(epic theme playing)

2
00:00:10.219 --> 00:00:13.014
♪ ♪

3
00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:21.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

4
00:00:47.465 --> 00:00:51.260
♪ ♪

5
00:01:50.486 --> 00:01:52.154
(solemn music playing)

6
00:01:54.824 --> 00:01:56.534
(birds chirping)

7
00:01:59.954 --> 00:02:01.998
(wind blowing)

8
00:02:16.679 --> 00:02:19.724
♪ ♪

9
00:02:48.544 --> 00:02:51.005
(indistinct chatter)

10
00:02:53.382 --> 00:02:55.217
(cookware clinking)

11
00:03:09.148 --> 00:03:10.983
♪ ♪

12
00:03:11.067 --> 00:03:11.525
Queen Alicent:
You're sure?

13
00:03:11.609 --> 00:03:13.194
(sobs)

14
00:03:16.697 --> 00:03:18.157
Talya:
With his own eyes. Your Grace.

15
00:03:26.749 --> 00:03:28.376
(sniffles) Uh...

16
00:03:30.336 --> 00:03:32.463
Stay here.
Tell. tell no one.

17
00:03:33.631 --> 00:03:36.300
Help me dress.

18
00:03:36.384 --> 00:03:38.177
♪ ♪

19
00:03:50.982 --> 00:03:52.566
Who knows?

20
00:03:56.028 --> 00:03:57.697
My handmaiden. Talya.

21
00:03:58.614 --> 00:04:01.659
Some of the servants.

22
00:04:05.621 --> 00:04:07.623
I saw him last night...

23
00:04:08.624 --> 00:04:11.669
before he...

24
00:04:14.797 --> 00:04:17.008
He told me he wished
for Aegon to be king.

25
00:04:25.850 --> 00:04:27.476
It is the truth.

26
00:04:28.394 --> 00:04:30.396
Uttered with his own lips.

27
00:04:30.479 --> 00:04:34.066
His last words to me and I
was the only one to hear it.

28
00:04:35.401 --> 00:04:36.736
And now he's dead.

29
00:04:38.821 --> 00:04:41.866
♪ ♪

30
00:05:07.016 --> 00:05:09.977
(sighs) What is it that could
not have waited an hour?

31
00:05:10.061 --> 00:05:11.687
Was Dorne invaded?

32
00:05:15.232 --> 00:05:16.984
The King is dead.

33
00:05:27.036 --> 00:05:29.497
We grieve
for Viserys the Peaceful...

34
00:05:30.831 --> 00:05:32.374
our sovereign...

35
00:05:34.668 --> 00:05:35.753
our friend.

36
00:05:39.799 --> 00:05:41.425
But he has left us a gift.

37
00:05:45.054 --> 00:05:49.141
With his last breath. he impressed
upon the Queen his final wish:

38
00:05:49.225 --> 00:05:52.686
that his son. Aegon...

39
00:05:52.770 --> 00:05:56.816
should succeed him
as Lord of the Seven Kingdoms.

40
00:05:59.068 --> 00:06:01.987
(thunder rumbles)

41
00:06:05.950 --> 00:06:08.202
Then we may proceed now
with the full assurance

42
00:06:08.285 --> 00:06:11.122
of his blessing
on our long-laid plans.

43
00:06:11.205 --> 00:06:13.124
Otto High tower: Yes.
There is much to be done.

44
00:06:13.207 --> 00:06:14.750
as we've previously discussed.

45
00:06:14.834 --> 00:06:16.877
Now. there are two
among the captains

46
00:06:16.961 --> 00:06:19.588
of the City Watch that
remain loyal to Daemon.

47
00:06:19.672 --> 00:06:22.341
Let us replace them.
Lord Lannister.

48
00:06:22.424 --> 00:06:23.801
Tyland Lannister:
The Treasury is well in hand.

49
00:06:23.884 --> 00:06:25.845
The gold will be divided
for safekeeping.

50
00:06:25.928 --> 00:06:26.887
Otto: Let ravens
be sent to our allies.

51
00:06:26.971 --> 00:06:29.348
River run and High garden.

52
00:06:29.431 --> 00:06:30.850
Am I to understand that
members of the small council

53
00:06:30.933 --> 00:06:34.645
have been planning secretly
to install my son without me?

54
00:06:34.728 --> 00:06:38.274
My Queen. there was no need to
sully you with darkling schemes.

55
00:06:38.357 --> 00:06:40.109
Lyman Beesbury:
I will not have this.

56
00:06:40.192 --> 00:06:42.236
To hear that you are plotting

57
00:06:42.319 --> 00:06:45.406
to replace the King's
chosen heir

58
00:06:45.489 --> 00:06:46.574
- with an imposter!
- Tyland: His firstborn son

59
00:06:46.657 --> 00:06:49.702
- is hardly an imposter.
- Lyman: Hundreds of lords

60
00:06:49.785 --> 00:06:52.454
and landed knights
swore fealty to the Princess.

61
00:06:52.538 --> 00:06:54.373
Tyland: That was some 20
years ago. Most of them now dead.

62
00:06:54.456 --> 00:06:55.791
Jasper Wylde:
You heard the Lord Hand.

63
00:06:55.875 --> 00:06:58.169
Plot or no.
the King changed his mind.

64
00:06:58.961 --> 00:07:01.672
I am six-and-seventy years old.

65
00:07:01.755 --> 00:07:06.218
I have known Viserys longer
than any who sit at this table.

66
00:07:06.302 --> 00:07:07.761
And I will not believe
that he said this

67
00:07:07.845 --> 00:07:13.976
on his deathbed. alone. with only
the. the boy's mother as a witness.

68
00:07:14.977 --> 00:07:17.021
This is seizure!

69
00:07:17.104 --> 00:07:19.523
It is theft!
It is treason!

70
00:07:19.607 --> 00:07:23.402
- At the least. it is...
- Mind your tongue. Lyman.

71
00:07:23.485 --> 00:07:25.946
The King was well last night...

72
00:07:26.030 --> 00:07:27.656
by all accounts.

73
00:07:28.949 --> 00:07:34.038
Which of you here can swear
that he died of his own accord?

74
00:07:34.121 --> 00:07:37.833
Which of us are you accusing
of regicide. Lord Beesbury?

75
00:07:37.917 --> 00:07:39.627
Lyman:
Whether it was one of you.

76
00:07:39.710 --> 00:07:42.254
or all of you. I care not.

77
00:07:42.338 --> 00:07:43.339
- I will have no part...
- Sit down!

78
00:07:43.422 --> 00:07:46.342
- Lyman: Ahh!
- Alicent: Ser Criston.

79
00:07:58.062 --> 00:08:01.482
Throw down your sword and
remove your cloak. Ser Criston.

80
00:08:03.442 --> 00:08:06.111
I am your Lord Commander.
Ser Criston.

81
00:08:06.195 --> 00:08:07.696
Cast down your sword.

82
00:08:07.780 --> 00:08:11.283
I will not suffer insults
to Her Grace the Queen.

83
00:08:11.367 --> 00:08:14.453
There was no insult to me. Ser
Criston. Y... Put aside your blade.

84
00:08:22.753 --> 00:08:25.547
- Has it come to this?
- Lord Commander. enough.

85
00:08:29.218 --> 00:08:33.806
- Let us have Lord Beesbury removed.
- Otto: No.

86
00:08:33.889 --> 00:08:37.142
The door remains shut
until we finish our business.

87
00:08:54.076 --> 00:08:55.703
Storm's End is of concern.

88
00:08:55.786 --> 00:08:59.164
We may not assume
the loyalty of Lord Borros.

89
00:08:59.248 --> 00:09:01.959
But he has four daughters.
all of them unmarried.

90
00:09:02.042 --> 00:09:05.129
- The right proposal...
- What of Rhaenyra?

91
00:09:05.212 --> 00:09:09.008
The former heir cannot. of
course. be allowed to remain free

92
00:09:09.091 --> 00:09:12.845
and draw support to her claim.

93
00:09:12.928 --> 00:09:15.389
- Alicent: You mean to imprison her.
- Otto: She and her family

94
00:09:15.472 --> 00:09:16.724
will be given the opportunity

95
00:09:16.807 --> 00:09:20.185
to publicly swear obeisance
to the new King.

96
00:09:20.269 --> 00:09:22.187
She will never bend the knee.

97
00:09:22.271 --> 00:09:25.024
Nor will Daemon. which you know.

98
00:09:30.446 --> 00:09:32.031
You plan to kill them.

99
00:09:36.368 --> 00:09:38.746
And all here accede to this.

100
00:09:38.829 --> 00:09:41.165
Grand Maester Orwyle: Your
father is correct. Your Grace.

101
00:09:41.248 --> 00:09:44.877
A living challenger invites
battle and bloodshed.

102
00:09:44.960 --> 00:09:46.879
It is unsavory. yes.

103
00:09:46.962 --> 00:09:50.382
But a sacrifice we must make
to secure Aegon's succession.

104
00:09:50.466 --> 00:09:53.385
And then there is
Daemon to consider.

105
00:09:53.469 --> 00:09:56.013
- The King wouldn't wish for any unsavory...
- But the King did not wish

106
00:09:56.096 --> 00:09:58.891
for the murder of his daughter!

107
00:09:58.974 --> 00:10:00.893
He loved her.
I will not have you deny this.

108
00:10:00.976 --> 00:10:02.936
- And yet...
- One more word. and I will have you removed

109
00:10:03.020 --> 00:10:04.980
from this chamber
and sent to the Wall!

110
00:10:15.658 --> 00:10:18.452
What do you suggest. Your Grace?

111
00:10:21.080 --> 00:10:22.790
- (sighs)
- Otto: Time is of the essence.

112
00:10:33.759 --> 00:10:35.636
Lord Commander We sterling...

113
00:10:36.553 --> 00:10:39.098
take your knights
to Dragons tone.

114
00:10:39.181 --> 00:10:41.016
Be quick and be clean.

115
00:10:55.364 --> 00:10:56.824
I am Lord Commander
of the Kings guard.

116
00:11:00.744 --> 00:11:03.789
I recognize no authority
but the King's.

117
00:11:04.873 --> 00:11:06.708
And until there is one...

118
00:11:09.169 --> 00:11:11.004
I have no place here.

119
00:11:12.381 --> 00:11:15.426
♪ ♪

120
00:11:22.891 --> 00:11:23.809
Princess Helaena:
It is our fate. I think.

121
00:11:23.892 --> 00:11:26.812
to crave always what
is given to another.

122
00:11:26.895 --> 00:11:31.191
If one possesses a thing.
the other will take it away.

123
00:11:31.275 --> 00:11:33.360
Yes. Princess.

124
00:11:33.861 --> 00:11:35.446
(door opens)

125
00:11:36.280 --> 00:11:37.656
Where is Aegon?

126
00:11:40.951 --> 00:11:42.661
N-Not here.

127
00:11:42.744 --> 00:11:43.871
He's not in his rooms.

128
00:11:51.670 --> 00:11:52.921
Father.

129
00:11:55.591 --> 00:11:56.675
(children babbling)

130
00:12:02.306 --> 00:12:03.932
What's happened?

131
00:12:10.147 --> 00:12:13.942
♪ ♪

132
00:12:18.989 --> 00:12:22.242
- Your father...
- There is a beast beneath the boards.

133
00:12:22.326 --> 00:12:24.411
Oh. my dearest love.

134
00:12:29.500 --> 00:12:31.877
(footsteps approach)

135
00:12:45.682 --> 00:12:47.226
Ser Erryk.

136
00:12:50.896 --> 00:12:51.688
Where's the Prince?

137
00:12:51.772 --> 00:12:54.483
Forgive me. Lord Hand.
I do not know.

138
00:12:54.566 --> 00:12:57.903
But you're sworn to protect him.

139
00:12:57.986 --> 00:12:59.738
He exploits his authority
to order me away.

140
00:12:59.821 --> 00:13:00.948
and then he evades me. my Lord.

141
00:13:05.827 --> 00:13:09.039
I believe he may have
left the Keep secretly.

142
00:13:09.122 --> 00:13:10.791
gone into the city.

143
00:13:10.874 --> 00:13:12.960
- Find him.
- (footsteps approach)

144
00:13:17.214 --> 00:13:19.758
Take no one else
but your brother.

145
00:13:19.841 --> 00:13:21.552
And remove your white cloaks.

146
00:13:21.635 --> 00:13:22.886
None can know who you are
or what you seek...

147
00:13:24.388 --> 00:13:26.765
including the Queen.

148
00:13:26.848 --> 00:13:28.767
My Lord.

149
00:13:28.850 --> 00:13:32.271
Bring him to me. and me alone.
Ser Erryk.

150
00:13:38.902 --> 00:13:39.987
(door locking)

151
00:13:42.447 --> 00:13:45.826
(tense music playing)

152
00:13:50.872 --> 00:13:53.917
What is the meaning of this?

153
00:13:59.965 --> 00:14:02.009
♪ ♪

154
00:14:13.353 --> 00:14:15.105
Guard. Guard!

155
00:14:15.188 --> 00:14:16.982
♪ ♪

156
00:14:29.578 --> 00:14:32.539
Prince Aegon's not to be found
within the castle walls. Your Grace.

157
00:14:32.623 --> 00:14:34.708
Your father has sent Ser
Erryk into the city to find him.

158
00:14:37.544 --> 00:14:40.297
Ser Erryk knows Aegon.
He has the advantage.

159
00:14:47.387 --> 00:14:50.140
I trust again to you.
Ser Criston.

160
00:14:50.223 --> 00:14:52.017
and to your loyalty.

161
00:14:52.100 --> 00:14:55.687
Aegon must be found. and
he must be brought to me.

162
00:14:55.771 --> 00:14:57.064
The very fate of the Seven
Kingdoms depends on it.

163
00:14:59.024 --> 00:15:02.903
Everything you feel for me...
as your Queen.

164
00:15:04.446 --> 00:15:07.699
I will not fail you.

165
00:15:07.783 --> 00:15:08.784
Prince Aemond:
I'll come with you.

166
00:15:08.867 --> 00:15:12.079
That would not be
my desire. Aemond.

167
00:15:12.162 --> 00:15:17.042
- If anything has happened...
- Cole needs me. Mother.

168
00:15:17.125 --> 00:15:20.379
Ser Erryk isn't the only one
who knows Aegon's doings.

169
00:15:25.092 --> 00:15:26.885
♪ ♪

170
00:15:30.138 --> 00:15:31.723
(door opens)

171
00:15:32.474 --> 00:15:34.601
(door closes)

172
00:15:34.685 --> 00:15:36.269
(bells tolling)

173
00:15:37.479 --> 00:15:39.564
(dog barking)

174
00:15:46.697 --> 00:15:48.323
Aemond: Aegon brought
me to the Street of Silk

175
00:15:48.407 --> 00:15:49.950
on my thirteenth name day.

176
00:15:50.033 --> 00:15:53.245
It was his duty
as my brother. he said.

177
00:15:53.328 --> 00:15:56.540
to ensure I was
as educated as he was.

178
00:16:00.544 --> 00:16:02.921
At least that's what
I understood him to mean.

179
00:16:06.341 --> 00:16:08.176
I don't follow.

180
00:16:08.260 --> 00:16:09.928
He said.
“Time to get it wet.”

181
00:16:10.011 --> 00:16:13.014
Every woman is
an image of the Mother.

182
00:16:13.098 --> 00:16:14.433
to be spoken of with reverence.

183
00:16:14.516 --> 00:16:17.352
(bell ringing)

184
00:16:23.483 --> 00:16:24.735
Sometime last night. we...

185
00:16:24.818 --> 00:16:28.238
misplaced
our drinking companion.

186
00:16:28.321 --> 00:16:31.783
Knowing that he has been. in the
past. a patron of your fine establishment.

187
00:16:31.867 --> 00:16:33.618
we thought to inquire here
as to his whereabouts.

188
00:16:33.702 --> 00:16:35.036
And describe him.

189
00:16:36.747 --> 00:16:38.874
That is a delicate matter.

190
00:16:39.708 --> 00:16:40.625
(softly)
You see. the man we seek

191
00:16:40.709 --> 00:16:42.961
is the young Prince Aegon.

192
00:16:43.044 --> 00:16:46.548
I may trust. I hope.
in the discretion of your trade.

193
00:16:46.631 --> 00:16:47.799
(chuckles)

194
00:16:47.883 --> 00:16:49.968
The Prince is not here.

195
00:16:50.051 --> 00:16:54.765
Has he been here?
Earlier. perhaps?

196
00:16:54.848 --> 00:16:58.894
- Quite a bit earlier. Years ago. in fact.
- But more recently?

197
00:17:00.687 --> 00:17:03.899
He does not frequent
the Street of Silk.

198
00:17:03.982 --> 00:17:06.151
His tastes are known to be...

199
00:17:06.735 --> 00:17:09.446
less discriminating.

200
00:17:10.238 --> 00:17:11.281
Meaning what?

201
00:17:12.866 --> 00:17:17.871
I wish you luck. good Ser.
And my best to your friend.

202
00:17:23.627 --> 00:17:26.004
How you've grown.

203
00:17:29.091 --> 00:17:32.135
Aemond: Hm.

204
00:17:33.720 --> 00:17:35.847
Otto:
Viserys amended his wishes.

205
00:17:35.931 --> 00:17:37.891
It's as simple as that.

206
00:17:39.226 --> 00:17:42.145
You once swore
your banners to Rhaenyra.

207
00:17:42.229 --> 00:17:44.189
You must now

208
00:17:44.272 --> 00:17:46.942
pledge them to the future king.

209
00:17:53.782 --> 00:17:59.037
I must confer first
with my house on this matter.

210
00:17:59.120 --> 00:18:02.165
You'll not leave this room
without declaring your intention.

211
00:18:11.800 --> 00:18:14.928
I am no oath breaker.

212
00:18:17.639 --> 00:18:19.474
I will not bend the knee.

213
00:18:26.731 --> 00:18:29.109
Otto: Anyone else?

214
00:18:41.162 --> 00:18:45.167
House Fell... keeps its
sworn oath to the Princess.

215
00:18:48.587 --> 00:18:50.672
Very well.

216
00:18:54.301 --> 00:18:57.095
♪ ♪

217
00:19:10.692 --> 00:19:11.902
Long live the King.

218
00:19:11.985 --> 00:19:14.821
All:
Long live the King.

219
00:19:22.579 --> 00:19:25.040
♪ ♪

220
00:19:25.123 --> 00:19:27.751
(ambient street noise)

221
00:19:35.300 --> 00:19:37.135
(indistinct chatter)

222
00:19:45.894 --> 00:19:48.772
Criston Cole: It seems you were
mistaken as to Aegon's habits.

223
00:19:48.855 --> 00:19:51.483
Aemond: He could be in
the hands of mercenaries.

224
00:19:51.566 --> 00:19:53.026
on a ship to Yi Ti.

225
00:19:53.985 --> 00:19:56.112
He could be dead.

226
00:19:56.196 --> 00:19:58.448
Let us hope. for your mother's
sake. that is not the case.

227
00:20:04.621 --> 00:20:06.456
(distant yelling)

228
00:20:14.422 --> 00:20:15.966
- Man 1: Let's have a look.
- (groaning)

229
00:20:16.049 --> 00:20:18.551
- Go on.
- Man 2: Come here. Come here!

230
00:20:18.635 --> 00:20:21.429
- Get in there. you little...
- (crowd cheering)

231
00:20:27.644 --> 00:20:28.853
Yeah!

232
00:20:30.146 --> 00:20:33.149
Come on!

233
00:20:33.441 --> 00:20:34.901
(child screams)

234
00:20:34.985 --> 00:20:36.403
(crowd exclaiming)

235
00:20:38.113 --> 00:20:41.199
(grunting) - Arryk
Cargyll: How old are they?

236
00:20:41.283 --> 00:20:44.828
Erryk Cargyll:
About 10 years. I should say.

237
00:20:44.911 --> 00:20:48.081
They have them grow
their nails and file the teeth.

238
00:20:48.164 --> 00:20:49.499
Makes them more formidable.

239
00:20:51.167 --> 00:20:54.754
- Come on!
- Prince Aegon spends many a night in this place.

240
00:20:54.838 --> 00:20:57.090
Do you see now what he is?

241
00:20:57.173 --> 00:20:58.466
You've not seen everything.

242
00:21:01.344 --> 00:21:02.929
(crowd cheering)

243
00:21:07.100 --> 00:21:10.020
- Aegon's?
- One of many. I'd wager.

244
00:21:13.606 --> 00:21:16.401
♪ ♪

245
00:21:26.661 --> 00:21:29.789
Aemond: Here I am. trawling
the city. ever the good soldier

246
00:21:29.873 --> 00:21:33.376
in search of a wastrel who's never
taken half an interest in his birthright.

247
00:21:36.212 --> 00:21:39.049
'Tis I the younger brother who
studies history and philosophy.

248
00:21:39.132 --> 00:21:40.759
it is I who trains
with the sword.

249
00:21:40.842 --> 00:21:41.801
who rides the largest
dragon in the world.

250
00:21:41.885 --> 00:21:44.262
It is I who should be...

251
00:21:47.766 --> 00:21:50.727
I know what it is to toil for
what others are freely given.

252
00:21:50.810 --> 00:21:52.562
Mm.

253
00:21:55.065 --> 00:21:57.692
And we can't find him. Cole.

254
00:21:57.776 --> 00:22:00.779
You are a decent man
with no taste for depravity.

255
00:22:00.862 --> 00:22:02.781
His secrets are his own...

256
00:22:02.864 --> 00:22:04.157
and he's welcome to them.

257
00:22:04.240 --> 00:22:06.951
I'm next in line to the throne.

258
00:22:07.035 --> 00:22:09.537
Should they come looking for me.

259
00:22:09.621 --> 00:22:11.289
I intend to be found.

260
00:22:21.216 --> 00:22:24.260
Ser Arryk: Something must
be done. Aegon is unfit to rule.

261
00:22:24.344 --> 00:22:26.179
You tolerated the Prince's
proclivities for years.

262
00:22:26.262 --> 00:22:27.180
Because it was
my sworn duty. Arryk.

263
00:22:27.263 --> 00:22:29.140
It's for the Hand
to find wisdom.

264
00:22:29.224 --> 00:22:32.310
We swore an oath
of service until death.

265
00:22:32.393 --> 00:22:35.313
Jayne:
A moment of your time. m'lords.

266
00:22:35.396 --> 00:22:37.357
You'll find no buyers
for your wares here.

267
00:22:41.861 --> 00:22:44.906
I can take you to Prince Aegon.

268
00:22:45.240 --> 00:22:48.243
Rather. I am sent by one
who knows where he is.

269
00:22:48.326 --> 00:22:49.452
Who'll tell you. for a price.

270
00:22:51.955 --> 00:22:54.582
Deliver him. and we'll
consider your price.

271
00:22:54.666 --> 00:22:59.546
My mistress will not treat
with the servants of the Keep...

272
00:22:59.629 --> 00:23:02.382
exalted though they may be.

273
00:23:02.465 --> 00:23:04.801
She'll trust this to
the Hand of the King only.

274
00:23:04.884 --> 00:23:06.886
Impossible.

275
00:23:06.970 --> 00:23:10.890
I think he will wish to hear what
the White Worm can tell him.

276
00:23:10.974 --> 00:23:13.059
(crowd cheering)

277
00:23:18.815 --> 00:23:21.651
(bells tolling)

278
00:23:27.115 --> 00:23:28.867
Knight:
Halt! Hold the gate!

279
00:23:28.950 --> 00:23:30.827
(horse neighs)

280
00:23:31.953 --> 00:23:33.204
Allun Caswell:
Let go of me!

281
00:23:33.288 --> 00:23:34.998
Larys Strong:
He was fleeing from the gate.

282
00:23:35.081 --> 00:23:35.874
Allun:
Do you know who I am?

283
00:23:35.957 --> 00:23:37.584
Larys:
A warning for the Princess.

284
00:23:37.667 --> 00:23:40.545
I'd wager.

285
00:23:40.628 --> 00:23:41.754
What say you?

286
00:23:43.131 --> 00:23:46.009
The Lord Confessor presumes.

287
00:23:47.510 --> 00:23:50.013
I have no love for the Princess.

288
00:23:50.096 --> 00:23:53.308
And where were you going then
with such urgency?

289
00:23:59.147 --> 00:24:01.274
Let the King's Justice take him.

290
00:24:05.612 --> 00:24:06.613
Allun: Let go of me!

291
00:24:06.696 --> 00:24:09.449
- No! This is not right!
- You did well. Lord Larys.

292
00:24:09.532 --> 00:24:13.286
- Allun: I will...
- Only my duty. my Lord Hand.

293
00:24:13.369 --> 00:24:14.537
Allun: (faintly)
Who do you think you are?

294
00:24:14.621 --> 00:24:16.831
You've spent many hours
with the Queen of late.

295
00:24:22.837 --> 00:24:28.134
There's no reason those hours
could not. in the end. benefit you.

296
00:24:30.011 --> 00:24:33.890
(solemn music playing)

297
00:24:58.081 --> 00:25:01.876
♪ ♪

298
00:25:24.941 --> 00:25:26.526
(sniffles)

299
00:25:46.921 --> 00:25:48.548
(door opens)

300
00:25:57.807 --> 00:26:00.977
I will do you the considerable
courtesy of assuming

301
00:26:01.060 --> 00:26:02.979
there is a good reason
for the outrage

302
00:26:03.062 --> 00:26:04.981
of my treatment
here this morning.

303
00:26:06.107 --> 00:26:08.568
My sincerest regrets
for the lack of ceremony.

304
00:26:11.988 --> 00:26:13.323
The King.

305
00:26:18.453 --> 00:26:21.205
And you are usurping the throne.

306
00:26:21.289 --> 00:26:23.207
It was my husband's dying wish.

307
00:26:23.291 --> 00:26:24.208
- (scoffs)
- Believe it or no.

308
00:26:24.292 --> 00:26:27.003
it is of no consequence.

309
00:26:27.086 --> 00:26:28.379
Aegon will be king.

310
00:26:31.966 --> 00:26:34.552
I came here to ask your support.

311
00:26:34.635 --> 00:26:38.181
Well. I must credit you
for your boldness.

312
00:26:38.264 --> 00:26:40.266
House Velaryon
has long allied itself

313
00:26:40.350 --> 00:26:42.643
with the Princess Rhaenyra
and what has it gained you?

314
00:26:44.729 --> 00:26:47.940
Your daughter dead...
alone in Pentos.

315
00:26:49.025 --> 00:26:50.818
Your son cuckolded.

316
00:26:50.902 --> 00:26:53.154
Rhaenyra's heirs
are none of yours.

317
00:26:54.447 --> 00:26:59.410
It is your husband who grasps
so heedlessly for the throne.

318
00:26:59.494 --> 00:27:01.287
And even he has abandoned you:

319
00:27:01.371 --> 00:27:03.998
gone these six long years
to fight a desperate battle.

320
00:27:04.082 --> 00:27:07.168
returning grievously.
if not mortally. wounded.

321
00:27:07.251 --> 00:27:09.879
leaving the Lady of Driftmark
to chart her course alone.

322
00:27:12.673 --> 00:27:15.593
The word of my house
is not fickle.

323
00:27:17.720 --> 00:27:20.807
No. But. dear cousin...

324
00:27:22.642 --> 00:27:26.771
you more than any soul alive
understand what I say now.

325
00:27:26.854 --> 00:27:28.481
Princess Rhaenys.
I loved my husband.

326
00:27:28.564 --> 00:27:31.401
but I will speak
the truth we both know.

327
00:27:32.110 --> 00:27:33.861
You should've been queen.

328
00:27:36.447 --> 00:27:38.616
I little thought to hear
those words from you.

329
00:27:38.699 --> 00:27:40.618
The Iron Throne was yours
by blood and by temperament.

330
00:27:40.701 --> 00:27:44.247
Viserys would've lived
his days a country lord.

331
00:27:44.330 --> 00:27:46.249
content to hunt
and study his histories.

332
00:27:46.332 --> 00:27:47.667
but... here we are.

333
00:27:51.045 --> 00:27:51.671
We do not rule

334
00:27:51.754 --> 00:27:55.174
but we may guide
the men that do.

335
00:27:55.258 --> 00:27:56.968
Gently...

336
00:27:57.051 --> 00:27:59.345
away from violence
and sure destruction

337
00:27:59.429 --> 00:28:02.223
- and instead toward peace.
- Ugh.

338
00:28:02.306 --> 00:28:05.476
Is it in the name of peace
that you've imprisoned me?

339
00:28:05.560 --> 00:28:07.728
- And what of my dragon?
- If we are over matched.

340
00:28:07.812 --> 00:28:10.148
Rhaenyra will be tempted to
strike us. and war will ensue.

341
00:28:10.231 --> 00:28:11.983
(sighs)

342
00:28:12.066 --> 00:28:15.319
Without your dragon. she
may be persuaded to negotiate.

343
00:28:16.821 --> 00:28:19.782
If it's Driftmark you want.
you shall have it

344
00:28:19.866 --> 00:28:24.287
for you and your granddaughters
to pass on as you see fit.

345
00:28:29.041 --> 00:28:30.751
You are wiser than
I believed you to be...

346
00:28:35.047 --> 00:28:37.341
Alicent High tower.

347
00:28:37.425 --> 00:28:40.928
A true queen counts
the cost to her people.

348
00:28:42.138 --> 00:28:45.725
And yet you toil still
in service to men.

349
00:28:45.808 --> 00:28:48.728
Your father.
your husband. your son.

350
00:28:50.605 --> 00:28:52.231
You desire not to be free.

351
00:28:52.315 --> 00:28:55.401
but to make a window
in the wall of your prison.

352
00:28:56.319 --> 00:28:59.947
Have you never
imagined yourself...

353
00:29:00.031 --> 00:29:03.075
on the Iron Throne?

354
00:29:03.367 --> 00:29:07.205
(tense music playing)

355
00:29:14.295 --> 00:29:16.172
I'll leave you
with your thoughts.

356
00:29:18.966 --> 00:29:20.885
Ring the bell when
you have an answer.

357
00:29:27.975 --> 00:29:29.810
(indistinct chatter)

358
00:29:34.565 --> 00:29:37.944
(ambient street noise)

359
00:29:45.368 --> 00:29:46.661
My Prince.

360
00:29:55.878 --> 00:29:59.882
You yourself are the mysterious
White Worm. I take it.

361
00:30:02.260 --> 00:30:06.138
Or are you simply a further
peel in this stinking onion?

362
00:30:08.057 --> 00:30:11.018
My condolences
on the passing of your king.

363
00:30:12.770 --> 00:30:14.814
♪ ♪

364
00:30:26.117 --> 00:30:27.451
Otto:
Where is Prince Aegon?

365
00:30:27.535 --> 00:30:34.208
I thought. the Prince is in Flea
Bottom where no one is to be trusted.

366
00:30:34.292 --> 00:30:36.586
I'd best secrete him
somewhere safe

367
00:30:36.669 --> 00:30:39.422
in case they come
looking for him.

368
00:30:39.505 --> 00:30:41.632
Where's the Prince?

369
00:30:41.716 --> 00:30:44.302
He is safely tucked away.

370
00:30:45.720 --> 00:30:49.265
I want an end to the savage use

371
00:30:49.348 --> 00:30:51.392
of children in Flea Bottom.

372
00:30:51.475 --> 00:30:54.729
They are forced to fight.
and worse...

373
00:30:54.812 --> 00:30:57.857
your gold cloaks take the
bribes given them to look away.

374
00:30:59.567 --> 00:31:01.902
An obscenity

375
00:31:01.986 --> 00:31:05.990
either tolerated
or ignored by the crown.

376
00:31:07.742 --> 00:31:09.702
I'll look into it.

377
00:31:09.785 --> 00:31:11.412
You have my word.

378
00:31:16.667 --> 00:31:18.419
When your plots ripen

379
00:31:18.502 --> 00:31:21.756
and you install your grandson
on the throne.

380
00:31:21.839 --> 00:31:25.009
remember it was me
who put him there.

381
00:31:25.092 --> 00:31:30.056
I could have killed him
as easily as a wasp on fruit.

382
00:31:30.139 --> 00:31:35.144
There is no power but what
the people allow you to take.

383
00:31:37.813 --> 00:31:38.898
I will remember.

384
00:31:40.483 --> 00:31:45.738
♪ ♪

385
00:32:02.963 --> 00:32:05.591
- (person coughs)
- Listen.

386
00:32:09.053 --> 00:32:10.596
(coughing)

387
00:32:12.264 --> 00:32:13.808
(groaning)

388
00:32:13.891 --> 00:32:15.810
No... No!

389
00:32:16.644 --> 00:32:18.688
No! Agh!

390
00:32:20.481 --> 00:32:22.274
(groans)

391
00:32:22.358 --> 00:32:23.943
(shouts)

392
00:32:26.320 --> 00:32:28.531
Where is the White Worm?

393
00:32:28.614 --> 00:32:29.782
Erryk:
She sold you for a price.

394
00:32:29.865 --> 00:32:30.991
And why have you paid it?

395
00:32:33.285 --> 00:32:35.830
I want my mother.

396
00:32:35.913 --> 00:32:37.623
Your grandfather. the Hand.

397
00:32:37.707 --> 00:32:39.625
will meet you
outside the city walls.

398
00:32:44.046 --> 00:32:45.131
(Aegon grunting)

399
00:32:47.842 --> 00:32:49.260
You flee what other men
die seeking. Aegon.

400
00:32:49.343 --> 00:32:51.387
(grunts)

401
00:32:53.806 --> 00:32:55.391
(grunting)

402
00:32:57.351 --> 00:32:59.186
(bells tolling)

403
00:33:00.438 --> 00:33:02.690
(grunts)

404
00:33:02.773 --> 00:33:04.775
♪ ♪

405
00:33:06.902 --> 00:33:08.028
I do regret this. friend.

406
00:33:17.872 --> 00:33:20.916
(swords clang)

407
00:33:24.712 --> 00:33:25.755
(grunts)

408
00:33:30.176 --> 00:33:32.678
(intense music playing)

409
00:33:36.015 --> 00:33:37.057
(grunting)

410
00:33:38.976 --> 00:33:41.645
Prince Aegon: No! Stop! No.

411
00:33:42.146 --> 00:33:44.482
(Aegon giggling)

412
00:33:45.733 --> 00:33:48.986
- I was hoping you disappeared.
- Is our father truly dead?

413
00:33:49.069 --> 00:33:51.363
Yes... and they're
going to make you king.

414
00:33:51.447 --> 00:33:54.158
- (spits)
- Agh!

415
00:33:54.241 --> 00:33:56.327
- Aegon: No!
- Erryk: Are you going to help me?!

416
00:33:56.410 --> 00:33:58.996
(grunting)

417
00:33:59.079 --> 00:34:01.540
Aegon: No! Let me go!

418
00:34:01.624 --> 00:34:02.666
Where's your brother. huh?

419
00:34:04.627 --> 00:34:06.337
Let me go!

420
00:34:06.420 --> 00:34:08.798
Brother! Ahh!

421
00:34:14.804 --> 00:34:16.388
Let me go!

422
00:34:17.056 --> 00:34:19.016
I have no wish to rule!

423
00:34:19.099 --> 00:34:21.727
No taste for duty!
I'm not suited.

424
00:34:21.811 --> 00:34:23.312
You'll get no argument from me.

425
00:34:23.395 --> 00:34:27.108
You let me go. I will
find a ship and sail away.

426
00:34:27.191 --> 00:34:28.275
never to be found.

427
00:34:32.279 --> 00:34:33.906
The Queen awaits.

428
00:34:38.786 --> 00:34:42.623
(tense music playing)

429
00:34:46.460 --> 00:34:49.255
♪ ♪

430
00:34:57.137 --> 00:34:58.722
(door opens)

431
00:35:04.728 --> 00:35:07.857
- Well played.
- None of this is a game.

432
00:35:07.940 --> 00:35:10.067
And yet you treat it as one.

433
00:35:11.402 --> 00:35:12.111
A charming contest.

434
00:35:12.194 --> 00:35:16.991
the... prize.
a pouch of silver.

435
00:35:21.620 --> 00:35:23.789
We have relied on one
another these many years.

436
00:35:23.873 --> 00:35:28.669
And now it is the good of
the family that we both desire.

437
00:35:28.752 --> 00:35:32.006
Whatever our differences.
our hearts remain as one.

438
00:35:34.008 --> 00:35:35.885
Our hearts were never one.

439
00:35:35.968 --> 00:35:37.595
I see that now.

440
00:35:37.678 --> 00:35:39.471
Rather. I have been a piece
that you moved about the board.

441
00:35:39.555 --> 00:35:45.895
If that is true. then I made you
Queen of the Seven Kingdoms.

442
00:35:45.978 --> 00:35:50.107
- Would you have desired it otherwise?
- How could I know?

443
00:35:50.190 --> 00:35:53.193
I wanted whatever you
impressed upon me to want.

444
00:35:54.737 --> 00:35:57.239
And now the debt comes due.

445
00:35:57.323 --> 00:36:00.284
- A debt you were happy enough to pay.
- A sacrifice.

446
00:36:00.367 --> 00:36:05.122
A sacrifice made for
the stability of the realm.

447
00:36:05.206 --> 00:36:07.291
No king has ever lived
that hasn't had to forfeit

448
00:36:07.374 --> 00:36:09.460
the lives of a few
to protect the many.

449
00:36:09.543 --> 00:36:11.754
Though I understand
your squeamishness.

450
00:36:11.837 --> 00:36:15.341
Reluctance to murder
is not a weakness!

451
00:36:19.094 --> 00:36:19.887
I have Aegon.

452
00:36:19.970 --> 00:36:22.598
We'll proceed now as I see fit.

453
00:36:25.559 --> 00:36:27.394
(Alicent sighs)

454
00:36:29.396 --> 00:36:32.524
We will send terms
to Rhaenyra on Dragons tone.

455
00:36:32.608 --> 00:36:35.653
True terms. such that she
may accept without shame.

456
00:36:35.736 --> 00:36:39.490
If she lives. her allies will
mass behind her banners.

457
00:36:39.573 --> 00:36:42.201
- looking for her return.
- Then she must not return.

458
00:36:43.577 --> 00:36:45.162
My husband would have
desired this mercy be shown

459
00:36:45.245 --> 00:36:47.998
- to his daughter.
- Your husband?

460
00:36:48.082 --> 00:36:50.834
Or you. his daughter's
childhood companion?

461
00:36:55.422 --> 00:36:58.467
Criston Cole will be named Lord
Commander of the Kings guard.

462
00:37:00.052 --> 00:37:02.596
My son will be anointed
tomorrow at dawn.

463
00:37:02.680 --> 00:37:06.183
The whole of King's Landing
must witness his ascent.

464
00:37:06.266 --> 00:37:09.895
He will assume authority.
There will be no more dithering.

465
00:37:09.979 --> 00:37:12.398
My son will take the crown of
his namesake. the Conqueror.

466
00:37:12.481 --> 00:37:14.566
and carry Blackfyre. his sword.

467
00:37:14.650 --> 00:37:18.112
Let the people remember the
ancient strength of House Targaryen.

468
00:37:22.199 --> 00:37:25.202
You look so much like
your mother in certain lights.

469
00:37:31.375 --> 00:37:32.918
(door opens)

470
00:37:34.211 --> 00:37:37.631
- (door closes)
- As you wish.

471
00:37:49.601 --> 00:37:51.437
Larys: Your Grace.

472
00:37:54.064 --> 00:37:58.444
The hour is late. Lord Larys.

473
00:37:58.527 --> 00:38:01.447
I've found out something
that you should know.

474
00:38:13.167 --> 00:38:17.337
Have you asked yourself.
I wonder...

475
00:38:17.421 --> 00:38:19.715
how it is... (grunts)

476
00:38:19.798 --> 00:38:21.467
That your father. the Hand...

477
00:38:22.843 --> 00:38:25.888
found Aegon first?

478
00:38:29.058 --> 00:38:31.143
(Alicent sighs)

479
00:38:58.754 --> 00:39:02.466
There is a web of spies
at work in the Red Keep.

480
00:39:02.549 --> 00:39:07.429
Along its threads travels news
of all our doings.

481
00:39:07.513 --> 00:39:12.976
Your father knows this.
but has left it in place.

482
00:39:13.060 --> 00:39:16.522
More than once. it has proved
advantageous to those willing to...

483
00:39:18.107 --> 00:39:20.400
feed the weaver.

484
00:39:21.902 --> 00:39:23.779
And this weaver watches me?

485
00:39:25.781 --> 00:39:27.825
Um...

486
00:39:47.678 --> 00:39:53.183
One of the little spiders
is your lady-in-waiting.

487
00:39:55.102 --> 00:39:57.980
- Talya?
- There are more like her.

488
00:39:58.063 --> 00:40:00.190
Even I do not know their number.

489
00:40:04.736 --> 00:40:09.032
There is one way
to destroy his advantage.

490
00:40:09.116 --> 00:40:12.077
It must be taken out
at the head.

491
00:40:13.787 --> 00:40:18.750
When the Queen dies.
the bees fly without purpose.

492
00:40:20.460 --> 00:40:23.463
Begging your pardon for the
turn of phrase. Your Grace.

493
00:40:23.547 --> 00:40:24.423
(sighs)

494
00:40:24.506 --> 00:40:28.760
I assume this task falls
within your expertise.

495
00:40:28.844 --> 00:40:31.889
If you wish it...

496
00:40:32.181 --> 00:40:33.682
it will be done.

497
00:40:36.059 --> 00:40:39.104
♪ ♪

498
00:41:03.378 --> 00:41:06.423
(Larys breathing heavily)

499
00:41:06.506 --> 00:41:07.549
♪ ♪

500
00:41:52.594 --> 00:41:55.305
Erryk:
Out of my way! (grunting)

501
00:42:02.604 --> 00:42:03.355
With me. Princess.

502
00:42:03.438 --> 00:42:05.983
I cannot let this
treachery stand.

503
00:42:10.237 --> 00:42:13.282
♪ ♪

504
00:42:44.313 --> 00:42:45.397
(birds cawing)

505
00:42:45.480 --> 00:42:48.650
- Where are we?
- Just south of King's Way.

506
00:42:50.527 --> 00:42:51.653
The Blackwater's this way.

507
00:42:53.822 --> 00:42:55.615
♪ ♪

508
00:43:20.724 --> 00:43:23.310
I won't leave Meleys.

509
00:43:23.393 --> 00:43:24.478
- If I could get to the Dragon pit. then...
- No.

510
00:43:24.561 --> 00:43:26.271
They'll expect you there.
Princess.

511
00:43:26.355 --> 00:43:29.232
You won't get past the gates.

512
00:43:29.649 --> 00:43:31.401
Now come.

513
00:43:31.485 --> 00:43:33.612
You must make for the
riverfront and find a ship.

514
00:43:33.695 --> 00:43:35.447
Before they know you've gone.

515
00:43:35.530 --> 00:43:37.616
Watch Captain: (shouting)
Move it! Go! Go!

516
00:43:37.699 --> 00:43:39.159
- (horse neighs)
- This way!

517
00:43:39.242 --> 00:43:41.912
Keep moving! That's right.

518
00:43:41.995 --> 00:43:43.288
That's right!

519
00:43:45.165 --> 00:43:46.333
- Onward!
- This way.

520
00:43:46.416 --> 00:43:49.294
Watch Captain:
Halt! Halt!

521
00:43:51.838 --> 00:43:53.757
Keep moving!

522
00:43:53.840 --> 00:43:55.675
(indistinct yelling)

523
00:43:58.553 --> 00:44:01.223
All of you. move forward!

524
00:44:03.809 --> 00:44:06.103
- (horse neighs)
- Keep moving!

525
00:44:06.186 --> 00:44:09.022
(indistinct yelling)

526
00:44:11.149 --> 00:44:13.193
(sheep bleating)

527
00:44:18.323 --> 00:44:20.909
Erryk:
Out of the way!

528
00:44:20.992 --> 00:44:22.953
Out of the way!

529
00:44:23.036 --> 00:44:25.330
(bells tolling)

530
00:44:25.414 --> 00:44:27.499
(indistinct chatter)

531
00:44:33.422 --> 00:44:35.507
(horses galloping)

532
00:44:37.676 --> 00:44:39.261
Hyah! Hyah!

533
00:44:43.181 --> 00:44:45.809
Alicent: Have the
decency to look grateful.

534
00:44:45.892 --> 00:44:49.438
Do you know what has been
done to give you this day?

535
00:44:52.649 --> 00:44:54.568
In an hour. you will be king.

536
00:44:54.651 --> 00:44:57.487
- And my father never wanted this.
- That's not true.

537
00:44:57.571 --> 00:44:59.656
He had 20 years to name me heir
and never did.

538
00:44:59.739 --> 00:45:02.576
Steadfastly. he upheld
Rhaenyra's claim.

539
00:45:02.659 --> 00:45:05.745
- He changed his mind.
- Oh. (chuckles)

540
00:45:07.747 --> 00:45:08.373
No...

541
00:45:08.457 --> 00:45:12.377
He could have. but he never did

542
00:45:12.461 --> 00:45:13.879
because he didn't like me.

543
00:45:15.380 --> 00:45:17.632
And yet. with his final breath.

544
00:45:17.716 --> 00:45:19.885
he whispered to me that you
should take his place on the throne.

545
00:45:22.721 --> 00:45:24.306
(chuckling)

546
00:45:41.114 --> 00:45:44.409
- Do not toy with me. Mother.
- I speak the truth.

547
00:45:51.708 --> 00:45:52.793
(distant chatter)

548
00:45:59.049 --> 00:46:01.343
Listen to me. Aegon.

549
00:46:01.426 --> 00:46:02.719
Your grandfather. the Hand.
will try to impress on you

550
00:46:02.802 --> 00:46:05.514
that Rhaenyra should be
put to the sword.

551
00:46:05.597 --> 00:46:08.725
You must reject this counsel.

552
00:46:08.808 --> 00:46:10.685
We must not rule with
cruelty and callousness.

553
00:46:10.769 --> 00:46:12.604
For all her faults.
she is your sister.

554
00:46:12.687 --> 00:46:15.190
- your. your father's daughter...
- Do you love me?

555
00:46:17.859 --> 00:46:20.445
- (bells tolling)
- You imbecile.

556
00:46:20.529 --> 00:46:23.114
Watch Captain: (shouting) Make
way for the royal wheelhouse!

557
00:46:24.783 --> 00:46:27.827
(indistinct yelling)

558
00:46:34.167 --> 00:46:35.627
(bells tolling)

559
00:46:39.214 --> 00:46:41.216
Watch Captain: (shouting)
Hey. hey. forward then.

560
00:46:42.884 --> 00:46:45.345
Guard:
Go on. move yourself! Come on!

561
00:46:47.347 --> 00:46:49.140
(horse neighs)

562
00:46:49.224 --> 00:46:51.059
(indistinct yelling)

563
00:46:58.358 --> 00:47:01.236
(captains. guards shouting)

564
00:47:03.029 --> 00:47:05.073
(bells tolling)

565
00:47:05.156 --> 00:47:06.950
(bird cawing)

566
00:47:08.535 --> 00:47:10.620
(indistinct chatter)

567
00:47:14.207 --> 00:47:17.043
(captains. guards shouting)

568
00:47:20.005 --> 00:47:21.965
(indistinct chatter)

569
00:47:22.048 --> 00:47:23.883
(bells tolling)

570
00:47:46.948 --> 00:47:49.492
Otto:
People of King's Landing...

571
00:47:49.576 --> 00:47:52.329
today is the saddest of days.

572
00:47:52.954 --> 00:47:56.166
Our beloved king...

573
00:47:56.249 --> 00:47:58.835
Viserys the Peaceful...

574
00:47:59.294 --> 00:48:01.630
is dead.

575
00:48:02.213 --> 00:48:04.215
(crowd murmuring)

576
00:48:07.010 --> 00:48:11.473
But it is also the most
joyous of days...

577
00:48:12.557 --> 00:48:15.226
for as his spirit left us...

578
00:48:17.354 --> 00:48:18.730
he whispered his final wish:

579
00:48:18.813 --> 00:48:23.943
that his firstborn son. Aegon...

580
00:48:25.278 --> 00:48:27.572
should succeed him.

581
00:48:27.656 --> 00:48:29.741
(crowd murmuring)

582
00:48:33.745 --> 00:48:35.455
(applause)

583
00:48:37.457 --> 00:48:39.793
Commander: Guards!

584
00:48:41.211 --> 00:48:43.546
Out of the way! Move!

585
00:48:52.055 --> 00:48:53.264
Commander: Halt!

586
00:48:53.348 --> 00:48:54.683
Turn!

587
00:48:58.812 --> 00:48:59.896
(horns blaring)

588
00:49:03.858 --> 00:49:05.902
Commander: Present...

589
00:49:05.985 --> 00:49:09.030
arms!

590
00:49:12.492 --> 00:49:15.328
(powerful music playing)

591
00:49:19.666 --> 00:49:22.711
♪ ♪

592
00:49:40.562 --> 00:49:43.648
Otto: It is your great
good fortune and privilege

593
00:49:43.732 --> 00:49:46.151
to be here to witness this:

594
00:49:48.111 --> 00:49:50.613
a new day for our city...

595
00:49:51.573 --> 00:49:53.616
a new day for our realm.

596
00:49:53.700 --> 00:49:58.872
A new king... to lead us.

597
00:49:58.955 --> 00:50:00.999
♪ ♪

598
00:50:44.918 --> 00:50:46.503
(person coughs)

599
00:50:56.346 --> 00:51:00.099
Septon Eustace: May the
Warrior give him courage.

600
00:51:03.019 --> 00:51:07.524
May the Smith lend strength
to his sword and shield.

601
00:51:09.776 --> 00:51:12.695
May the Father
defend him in his need.

602
00:51:15.156 --> 00:51:19.911
May the Crone
lift her shining lamp

603
00:51:19.994 --> 00:51:23.289
and light his way to wisdom.

604
00:51:23.373 --> 00:51:24.958
(person coughing)

605
00:51:47.564 --> 00:51:49.065
Criston:
The crown of the Conqueror.

606
00:51:49.148 --> 00:51:51.192
passed down through generations.

607
00:51:51.276 --> 00:51:53.111
(Aegon breathes deeply)

608
00:52:09.294 --> 00:52:11.713
Let the Seven bear witness:

609
00:52:11.796 --> 00:52:14.591
Aegon Targaryen is the
true heir to the Iron Throne.

610
00:52:14.674 --> 00:52:17.510
(crowd murmuring)

611
00:52:50.501 --> 00:52:55.214
All hail His Grace. Aegon.

612
00:52:55.298 --> 00:52:57.133
Second of his Name.

613
00:52:57.216 --> 00:53:00.803
King of the Andals and the
Rhoynar and the First Men.

614
00:53:00.887 --> 00:53:03.222
Lord of the Seven Kingdoms

615
00:53:03.306 --> 00:53:05.975
and Protector of the Realm.

616
00:53:08.061 --> 00:53:10.730
- (bells tolling)
- Aegon the King!

617
00:53:11.397 --> 00:53:14.651
(crowd applauds. cheers)

618
00:53:17.820 --> 00:53:19.864
♪ ♪

619
00:53:47.475 --> 00:53:49.060
(cheering)

620
00:53:49.811 --> 00:53:52.855
♪ ♪

621
00:54:13.084 --> 00:54:15.253
Crowd: Aegon the
King! Long live Aegon!

622
00:54:20.508 --> 00:54:23.428
- (crowd screaming)
- (Meleys roars)

623
00:54:26.848 --> 00:54:28.891
(roaring)

624
00:54:33.980 --> 00:54:35.523
(screaming)

625
00:54:38.234 --> 00:54:39.819
(roars)

626
00:54:42.155 --> 00:54:44.240
(footsteps thudding)

627
00:54:44.323 --> 00:54:46.075
(screaming)

628
00:54:50.663 --> 00:54:53.499
(intense music playing)

629
00:54:58.212 --> 00:54:59.756
(roars)

630
00:55:09.474 --> 00:55:12.018
♪ ♪

631
00:55:12.101 --> 00:55:13.936
(screaming)

632
00:55:17.857 --> 00:55:20.693
Open the doors!

633
00:55:27.909 --> 00:55:29.994
Open the doors!

634
00:55:34.874 --> 00:55:36.209
Get Helaena.

635
00:55:36.876 --> 00:55:38.461
(roars)

636
00:55:41.923 --> 00:55:44.133
♪ ♪

637
00:56:01.317 --> 00:56:03.361
(screeches)

638
00:56:20.628 --> 00:56:23.422
♪ ♪

639
00:56:26.592 --> 00:56:28.177
(screeches)

640
00:56:32.723 --> 00:56:34.267
(door closes)

641
00:56:39.147 --> 00:56:42.191
♪ ♪

641
